features: ELEVATE YOUR BATHROOM SANCTUARY - Immerse your bathroom in tranquility with our premium Sweet Water Decor Bathroom Reed Diffuser Set. Crafted with care from sustainable materials, enjoy a spa-like atmosphere with our specialized bathroom reed diffuser featuring Sea Salt Citrus & Musk Amber scents.

The high-quality reeds efficiently disperse captivating fragrances, providing a consistent and long-lasting scent, transforming your bath time into a luxurious retreat.

TAILORED FOR BATHROOMS - Specifically crafted for smaller spaces, our bathroom reed diffuser combats unwanted odors, creating a soothing atmosphere. Embrace the perfect blend of essential oils, turning your self-care routine into a cherished and rejuvenating experience.

AROMATHERAPY ELEGANCE - Experience the power of aromatherapy with our compact and stylish small reed diffuser. Perfectly sized for bathroom countertops or shelves, it adds sophistication while delivering a constant stream of your favorite essential oil fragrances.

ENJOY ENDORSED CONTENTMENT - Immerse yourself in the enduring, secure, and enchanting fragrances of our Sweet Water Decor oil reed diffuser set, introducing an extra layer of luxury to your daily bathroom routine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Smells and looks great!
reviews.reviewText: The smell is great and I love the simplicity of the bottle. Looks nice and modern too. A little pricey but hoping it lasts a decent amount.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Overpowers any bathroom odors!
reviews.reviewText: Not only does this naturally smell amazing, but it will overpower any nasty bathroom smells.I have a cat and I keep her litter box in the bathroom. Despite cleaning out her litter box every day, it will still smell like ammonia. I was looking for something to overpower the smell and bought the coconut and mango diffuser. It works so well!! My bathroom smells so fresh now

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I LOVE this product. I get a lot of compliments whenever people come to my home because it smells so good. The scent easily fills a medium sized room and it lasts for months. Whenever I run out I immediately buy another one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: pros: simple, clean and very effective.cons: a tad to sweet/commercial smelling.I will still continue to hunt for that spa like real clean non commercial scent.This came close. Nice- but will not buy again or gift this. Too commercial smelling.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love this reed diffuser! This is a good alternative for people trying to get away from toxic candles but still want their house to smell good. I am very sensitive to smells so it's nice that I can add or take away a reed and it changes the strength of the smell that gets released. This smells like a clean air bnb on the beach. It also arrived quickly and was packaged nicely to avoid potential damage in the mail. Will be purchasing again!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Barely smell it
reviews.reviewText: I'm disappointed because I love this scent but you can barely smell it unless you put it up to your nose! I have a small bathroom and was hoping after a few days it would've projected a stronger smell. Not sure if I got a bad batch, but I definitely don't think it's worth the money if the smell is practically nonexistent :(

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lasts a long time!
reviews.reviewText: I’ve had this sucker for over 6 months at this point and she still has a couple inches of diffuser left. I switch the reeds every month/every couple months and the scent is very strong for the first couple days and then relaxes into a pleasant background smell until I switch then reeds again. Very happy with this and love the smell, I got Spa Day. Worth the price for how long it’s lasted IMO.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars I was sensitive to the fragrance, not sure if it's phthalate-free
reviews.reviewText: I'm sensitive to fragrances, but there are many brands that work for me like Soyworx, Opalhouse at Target, etc.I tried this excited to see it listed as phthalate-free, but it's giving me symptoms. Had to put the cap back on to get it to stop affecting me. Having to return it. I wouldn't get it if you are sensitive to fragrances.
